      <para id="idm55872142096">This <m:math xmlns:m="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML"><m:semantics><m:mrow><m:mi>H</m:mi><m:mo stretchy="false">(</m:mo><m:mi>z</m:mi><m:mo stretchy="false">)</m:mo></m:mrow><m:annotation encoding="math/tex">H(z)</m:annotation></m:semantics></m:math>, which is a rational function in terms of <m:math xmlns:m="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML"><m:semantics><m:mrow><m:mi>z</m:mi></m:mrow><m:annotation encoding="math/tex">z</m:annotation></m:semantics></m:math>, is called the system's <term><emphasis>transfer function</emphasis></term>.</para>
